cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.CV 

This paper is about a new reinforcement learning environment for training agents to play football in a 3D simulator. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is focused on the development of algorithms and models for learning from data. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.GR (Graphics), and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper involves the use of advanced physics-based simulation, multiplayer and multi-agent experiments, and the development of scenarios and benchmarks for testing and evaluating reinforcement learning algorithms.
